column5: We're still having fun chasing walleyes around on Lac Seul here in Northwestern Ontario.   This time of year we're getting fish in 20-35 FOW.  Mornings have been best for us and jigging is outproducing set lines 3:1.      My buddy Graham with one from his set line.           Pretty good numbers of fish but we didn't see one over 22" the last 2 days.  I know I keep saying this but it's getting close to trout time.  Hopefully by the weekend we'll get out after them.  Tight lines all,  Ben
Great Report!  Looks like you had a blast the last two days!
WOW Ben got to love catching them eyes..... beautiful Great report and good job Thanks for sharing Leechman
wow they grow them big up that way  cheers!
Wow, nice fat fish.  So jealous of you Northwestern Ontarians and your amazing Pickerel fishery!
Another great outing Ben !!  Somethings missing.... lol
Way to go bud. Your posts are driving me nuts though LOL!
I'm with solo.......man, you guys get some nice fish up there!!!  Can't wait for a trout report, I'm sure you'll do it justice!!!  Sinker
WTG again boys...nice eyes...wow....Lac Seul is just the best.
A happy Elton John tune comes into my head..... B-B-B-Bennie and Eyes......  What a fishery out there man.  More good fish from ya.
Great report.. those are some fat 'eyes..  Keep posting those Lac Seul reports dude.. I love em, and I really miss the lake..
Great pickeral fishing!  Jiggin is the key I take it ! Good work guys.
I didn't want to look. Kind of figured what I would see. Ha ....I was right. Now I want to go there. Great fish Ben!

Being from a walleye starved area yet  a trout  infested area I often laugh how I crave the eyes yet you (not you personally)at times hunt what we call grease ballls!  lol   I refuse to fish lakers and only target the square tails and get them in abundance and pay money to fish perch and walleye!  Funny!
Wow...those are some nice eyes Ben!!...what a great part of Ontario to live at and fish in!!!!!
